			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3991&amp;sid=4d19f69e3fe6d73905fc997097969e13">kernelcode</a></strong> &raquo; Sun Jun 03, 2012 11:43 am </div>

			

			<div class="content">I put stuff in /etc/rc.local if I want it to run on boot - it will run with root privileges  (I think you could use sudo to stop that), and will run before login.<br />The advantage in my mind is that you aren't leaving a logged-in terminal (though maybe you could automatically log out with your method too?)</div>

			

