			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=8015&amp;sid=4d19f69e3fe6d73905fc997097969e13">Joe Schmoe</a></strong> &raquo; Sun Jun 03, 2012 11:54 am </div>

			

			<div class="content">It's funny how that goes - one man's meat is another man's poison.<br /><br />The *benefit* of doing it this way is that it runs visibly, meaning that you can see it running right there in the virtual console - and this is critical if it is interactive.<br /><br />It is also true that when you put it into the /etc/rc* sequence, if it fails, it gums up your booting process (and this can be fatal).  You have to be careful what you put there.  Human frailty and all that...</div>

			<div id="sig90836" class="signature">Never answer the question you are asked.  Rather, answer the question you <span style="font-style: italic">wish</span> you had been asked.<br /><br />- Robert S. McNamara - quoted in &quot;Fog of War&quot; -</div>

